I brought my niece to the avenue cafe because it is very similar in style and atmosphere to her coffee houses in Portland,Oregon. She was very happy with the variety of organic juices and vegan food options. The staff was very friendly and readily answered any menu questions. The food was brought out very quickly and was made to order. I had a little problem with The latte not being warm enough for me, but the management were very fast to provide excellent customer service to rectify The issue. I would go back again even with all The construction going on St. Charles Avenue.  The Avenue Cafe is cozy and casual. The laid back vibe of the staff and decor lends itself to people working on laptops, having a quick bite, and just stopping by to have coffee and conversation.  The family-friendly layout allows kids to be active, but not distracting to other customers. I didn't feel rushed to eat and run. Good job and that's why they received 4 stars.

We were displaced by a fire and spent two weeks in nearby hotels, so I've visited Avenue Cafe every day for two weeks.  The cafe is always clean, never too crowded, and affords a great place to work on a laptop (multiple outlets).  The coffee is delicious, as is the food. In fact, yesterday I had the single most delicious tuna sandwich I've ever had in a restaurant.  The staff are very friendly and the owner is hands-on and clearly knows what he is doing. They compost and recycle all their waste, and even provide glassware instead of plastic cups for the self-serve water.  There are three metered parking spaces outside, but free parking along nearby side streets is available.  They're open from 6:30am to 9:00pm.

Apple goat cheese scones. Sandwiches with quality meats and artisan cheeses. The best quality cinnamon rolls I've ever had, an orange flavored one I miss to this day.  The owners are the friendliest I've met, offering to let me borrow their personal coffee books, and on my last day in New Orleans after living their for years, gave me food and coffee on the house.
